ZH: 1. 现代科技逐渐开始替代传统的手工制作方式。
EN: 1. Modern technology is gradually replacing traditional handmade production methods.

ZH: 2. 他被替代了，因为他表现得不够出色。
EN: 2. He was replaced because he didn't perform well enough.

ZH: 3. 这种新型药物能够替代传统的治疗方式。
EN: 3. This new medication can substitute traditional treatment methods.

ZH: 4. 这个自动化系统将替代人工操作。
EN: 4. This automated system will replace manual operation.

ZH: 5. 这个应用程序可以替代传统的纸质日记本。
EN: 5. This application can replace traditional paper notebooks.

ZH: 6. 他被替代的消息让他感到沮丧。
EN: 6. The news of his replacement made him feel discouraged.

ZH: 7. 这个机器人可以替代人类完成繁重的工作。
EN: 7. This robot can substitute humans in performing heavy tasks.

ZH: 8. 电子邮件正逐渐替代传统的信函沟通。
EN: 8. Emails are gradually replacing traditional letter communication.

ZH: 9. 这家公司决定替代旧的生产设备。
EN: 9. This company has decided to replace the old production equipment.

ZH: 10. 这个应用程序的目标是替代传统的营销方式。
EN: 10. The goal of this application is to replace traditional marketing methods.

ZH: 11. 这项技术有望替代传统的能源来源。
EN: 11. This technology is expected to substitute traditional energy sources.

ZH: 12. 在数字音乐的时代，CD逐渐被数字音乐替代。
EN: 12. In the era of digital music, CDs are gradually being replaced by digital music.

ZH: 13. 这个新发明将替代目前的电池技术。
EN: 13. This new invention will replace current battery technologies.

ZH: 14. 在实验中，化学药剂被一种天然替代品取而代之。
EN: 14. In the experiment, the chemical reagent is replaced by a natural alternative.

ZH: 15. 新型洗衣机可以替代手洗衣物，更加省力。
EN: 15. The new washing machine can substitute hand washing clothes, making it easier.

ZH: 16. 这个应用程序的目的是为用户替代繁琐的任务。
EN: 16. The purpose of this application is to replace tedious tasks for users.

ZH: 17. 社交媒体逐渐替代传统媒体成为人们获取信息的首选渠道。
EN: 17. Social media is gradually replacing traditional media as people's preferred channel for obtaining information.

ZH: 18. 高速铁路对飞机出行产生了替代效应。
EN: 18. High-speed rail has had a substitution effect on air travel.

ZH: 19. 这本电子书是纸质书籍的替代品。
EN: 19. This e-book is a substitute for printed books.

ZH: 20. 健康饮品逐渐替代了碳酸饮料的受欢迎程度。
EN: 20. Healthy drinks are gradually replacing the popularity of carbonated beverages.
